# Blog Resource Audit (90+ Gate)

When creating or editing blog posts or AI career guides, follow the **blog-resource-audit** skill (`.cursor/skills/blog-resource-audit/SKILL.md`).

## Non-negotiables

- **Do not approve** articles scoring below **90/100**.
- Use **searchable plain job titles** in titles/H1 (not invented titles alone).
- Every career guide must include: definition, key takeaways, 6+ FAQs, future/AI block, checklist, natural Digni bridge.
- AI career guides (#1–26): use `audit-configs.ts` helpers; batch updates OK when auditing the full library.
- Flagship posts in `content/blog/en.ts`: process one slug at a time; update `content/blog/ARTICLE-AUDIT-QUEUE.md` after each.

## Career guide implementation

Reuse helpers in `lib/ai-career-jobs/custom-articles/shared-sections.ts`. Title/meta defaults: `lib/blog/article-intent.ts` + `displayJobTitle()`. Site positioning: `lib/positioning/clarity-framework.ts` (Grow → Learn → Scale). Wire new sections in `bodies-part1.ts` / `bodies-part2.ts` and `meta.ts` when titles need search-demand fixes.

## Publishing

Respect `blog-publishing.mdc` for dates and locale parity when touching `content/blog/*.ts`.
